{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"From East-end","author":"East-end"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"3a1b80a0-8711-5a42-8862-c84a48303ce6","excerpt":"In creating blog, I had to choice what is the best way to my blog. At first, WordPress came up in my mind. It’s so popular and easy to use…","html":"<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/logo-gatsby-3c37ea0a2611c7feda7ebef2ef78f554-30631.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 42.0625%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Gatsby Logo\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/logo-gatsby-3c37ea0a2611c7feda7ebef2ef78f554-f8fb9.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/logo-gatsby-3c37ea0a2611c7feda7ebef2ef78f554-e8976.jpg 148w,\n/static/logo-gatsby-3c37ea0a2611c7feda7ebef2ef78f554-63df2.jpg 295w,\n/static/logo-gatsby-3c37ea0a2611c7feda7ebef2ef78f554-f8fb9.jpg 590w,\n/static/logo-gatsby-3c37ea0a2611c7feda7ebef2ef78f554-85e3d.jpg 885w,\n/static/logo-gatsby-3c37ea0a2611c7feda7ebef2ef78f554-d1924.jpg 1180w,\n/static/logo-gatsby-3c37ea0a2611c7feda7ebef2ef78f554-30631.jpg 1600w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>In creating blog, I had to choice what is the best way to my blog.<br>\nAt first, WordPress came up in my mind. It’s so popular and easy to use.\nBut I didn’t have to multifunctional one and wanted to write front-end.\nThen I read some articles and found\n<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salted_duck_egg\">Gatsby.js</a>. So I gonna describe the reason for choosing.</p>\n<h2>1. Static site</h2>\n<p>Main reason is Gatsby.js is static site generator, not dynamic site like WordPress.\nWordPress is CMS and creates database. It needs update plugin for security. But I might not be access this blog every day, so management seems to be troublesome in WordPress. At this point, static site generator don’t have to care about update well.</p>\n<p>Also, static site is fast. It’s not need database, just web pages. And I didn’t need authentication, I choose this.</p>\n<h2>2. React-based</h2>\n<h2>3.</h2>","frontmatter":{"title":"Create this blog with Gatsby.js","date":"October 08, 2018"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog-using-gatsby/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/about-this-blog/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"About this blog"}},"next":null}}